[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'You know, it\'s interesting being a creator and obviously working with a lot of AI tools. You know, I often do get the question, "Are you worried that AI is going to replace you?" And look, while that\'s a question that impacts far beyond like guy with a YouTube channel, when it comes to creators and creatives,'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I mean the answer for me is always no. In fact, it\'s actually much more interesting to me given the, you know, 400 somewhat videos I\'ve done on this channel, how AI can help, not replace. And to that, I\'ve actually got a pretty'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'interesting use case starring channel fan favorite flamethrower girl. And it\'s extra interesting because it almost worked. We\'ll take a look at the why, the how, and the failure point, which spoilers was actually me.'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, kicking off with well, the failure point because I I mean I think that\'s the most honest and actually provides a bit of a through line here. The other week, as many of you know, I was at Google I/O. I do love traveling to big'

[00:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'events, meeting so many of you in person, and hanging out with my fellow creators. But, between the travel, the hotel rooms, and uh like all the event stuff, it is hard to juggle getting a video out. So, the plan was to use flamethrower girl as kind of a newsdesk'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'host for a midweek video uh utilizing HeyGen, who uh just as an FYI, were kind enough to sponsor today\'s video. The whole idea here was that well, it was kind of an interesting twist as well,'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you can check it out. I did build out the opening. Let\'s take a look at that real quick. Well, it\'s been a pretty crazy week with a lot of news going on, especially with Google I/O going on right now. Uh and you know what? That gives me an idea.'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Why don\'t we do this on location instead? But, you know what? I did leave somebody back at the studio for all of the rest of the news. &gt;&gt; Yep. Since Tim is off at I/O, I guess it\'s time for a flamethrower girl'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'takeover. &gt;&gt; So, the concept here was that this was a sort of a hybrid video in which uh flamethrower girl could deliver whatever breaking news was happening, and in the back end of the video, I could do on'

[01:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'location I/O reporting. We\'ll talk about the Flamethrower Girl build over on HeyGen in just a little bit, plus some other interesting things that I found. But just to give you an idea of kind of where my head space was when I was at'

[02:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'IO, you know, HeyGen also has a mobile app. So, you know, in my mind I was like, well, I could I could cover news stories sort of prompt in a script and then, you know, generate essentially while there. So, of course the question'

[02:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is, well, what happened? Well, I mean, honestly it had nothing to do with technology and everything to do with a slow news week. Yeah, the thing that I did not factor in was that Google was essentially going to dominate the news cycle that week and I really didn\'t have'

[02:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a plan B. Now, would it have worked? I mean, I tend to think so from a technical standpoint. I mean, I everything would have been fine. We\'ll see more as we go along, but I mean, avatars have come a long way in the last'

[02:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'few months. And as for, well, you guys, I I mean, I think you would have found it fun. If you\'re new here, very briefly, Flamethrower Girl is a long-running, I guess like meta character on the channel. She was originally born, that\'s weird to say, as'

[02:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a Midjourney example about two years ago during a period where I thought that grandmas with flamethrowers were pretty funny. I still think that grandmas with flamethrowers are pretty funny. Comments lit up on her first appearance and I'

[03:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'mean, ever since then she sort of served as a benchmark avatar for AI image and video technology and has evolved from a 2D character to, well, I mean, starring in her own short film. Part of that, and I don\'t really overanalyze this, but I I'

[03:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'do think that it resides in like the metaness of her. She can essentially appear in any example and she can break the fourth wall. So, you know, co-hosting a short or a news segment does not seem out of place for her. In fact, let\'s actually let\'s quickly check'

[03:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'out a short that I made earlier this week with HeyGen featuring her. &gt;&gt; Flamethrower Girl here. Tim\'s away from his desk, so I\'m filling in via HeyGen. We\'ll talk about that in just a sec, but did you know that Google\'s Genie 3, the'

[03:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'world simulator that they released last year, now has access to Google Street View. It\'s pretty neat, but where things get really interesting is when you run a Genie 3 output through the new Omni model. That\'s not only going to increase'

[04:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'all the details in the generation, but you\'ll also notice that it adds real-world details in. Just going to show, like Jensen said, in the future, every pixel will be generated. Maybe a'

[04:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'little like me. If you want to learn more about how this video was made, or try out HeyGen for yourself, hit the link down below. &gt;&gt; Now, did you hear some of my like cadence and patterns in there? Yes, you did. Uh we\'ll get to that in just a'

[04:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'minute. But, uh as far as the build over on HeyGen, so obviously the you know, the base level of her avatar is a image edit of her, you know, sitting. It\'s actually right here. And what\'s kind of cool is over on HeyGen that you can'

[04:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'actually generate up alternate looks if you want to as well. Actually, uh business suit flamethrower girl we\'re going to see in a little bit. They\'ve also added in the ability to train up or improve your model as well. I presume this is a LoRA. If you don\'t know what a'

[04:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'LoRA is, I don\'t worry about it. Uh essentially just, you know, upload between 10 and 30 images, and um your your avatar will like be more consistent. So, yeah. I mean, we have come a long'

[05:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'way since like V1 AI avatars. Uh it\'s funny, people in the comments are always like, "Aren\'t you an AI avatar?" And like looking at this, I mean, I might be. That I I\'m not. Uh that you know, if you could if I were an AI avatar, why'

[05:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'would I choose this? I could be anybody. Uh okay, let\'s go head back over to flamethrower girl. Uh you guys see me enough. So, since she is an AI character, what I ended up doing was grabbing uh a few outputs of her just'

[05:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'talking, uh and then stringing those together and utilizing that uh for voice training. Over here on HeyGen, uh there\'s actually a couple of different options that you can run voices under uh including 11 Labs, Fish, uh Panda,'

[05:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Starfish, and Mockingbird. Uh and then each of these have sort of their own little variations and sliders, and you can improve the voice by kind of prompting along with it. Now, once you have your avatar built out, there\'s'

[06:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'actually a couple of really interesting different ways that you can go about it here. Um you can actually choose your delivery style here um in direct voice and like literally like you are directing the voice. Uh you can text'

[06:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'prompt here or add in some keywords. Uh the other uh the two more interesting ones to me, uh auto enhance. Like in this case, it is a shorter sentence, so it just kind of put a chuckle in there. The other one that I the one that we'

[06:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'used earlier and I think that uh you guys definitely heard was uh mirror voice here. So, uh in this, I can just hit record. I can say, "Hey, I\'m Flamethrower Girl, and I\'m talking right now, and I\'m saying some stuff, and I'

[06:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'like I did before, I probably should have prepared something." &gt;&gt; I can say, "Hey, I\'m Flamethrower Girl, and I\'m talking right now, and I\'m saying some stuff, and I like I did before, I probably should have prepared something."'

[06:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; To me, that\'s the most interesting avatar use case. Although, you know, I should say that I should probably take some acting classes and, you know, write some more Flamethrower Girl centric dialogue so that she doesn\'t sound exactly like me. The other really interesting thing is that they have an'

[07:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'agent feature in which you can, you know, cast your avatar into uh different scenarios with uh templates and whatnot. Uh I did run one of these. This is just a straight-up one shot, so um just to see what it\'s like. I gave it the prompt of uh Flamethrower Girl essentially uh'

[07:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'complaining about what it\'s like to be uh working for me as an AI avatar. &gt;&gt; Hey everyone, Flamethrower Girl here. You probably think life as an AI co-host on Theoretically Media is all digital'

[07:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'bliss and easy renders, but the reality, it\'s a lot more work than you\'d imagine. Mostly because my boss is, well, let\'s just say he\'s organizationally'

[07:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'challenged. I\'m basically his personal assistant, project manager, and therapist all in one. I spent 4 hours yesterday just trying to find where he saved the script for this very video. It was in a folder named stuff. If you see'

[07:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'him in the comments, tell him the AI is considering unionizing. Catch you in the next one. If I can find the camera. &gt;&gt; That is brutal. What\'s wrong with the folder named stuff, too? This is where'

[08:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'all your stuff goes. So, what\'s kind of cool, again, that was all one shot. No cherry-picking at all. And I mean, kind of impressed with what it came up with. I will say that this shot I was not necessarily the biggest fan of. But'

[08:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'again, what\'s kind of cool is that you can kind of go into edit here and just re-prompt for something else as well. So, yeah, very very easy to edit these on the fly. So, I would say I don\'t have time to go through everything that'

[08:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'HeyGen has to offer, but I will say if you haven\'t been there in a while, there\'s a surprising amount of new stuff there, including the ability, obviously, to translate your video into 175 other languages, plus the ability to take your'

[08:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'characters out and like on location. So, after all of that, I mean, the question goes back to, would this whole thing have worked in a full video, you know, using flamethrower girl as a virtual co-host? I mean, I tend to think that it'

[08:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'would. Last time we did a short with her and actually with HeyGen\'s previous version, it hit like 24,000 views. But again, I think that\'s only because well, I mean, you guys know her. This is something that obviously goes around'

[09:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'like the AI video circles, as I like to call it, the 2B tsunami of AI-generated videos. You know, some will be good, some will be slop, well, kind of like real videos. And while in like the vertical world, we\'re certainly going to'

[09:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'see a lot of brand AI influencers in short-form content, you know, I don\'t necessarily know if that\'s going to transition into long-form. But that\'s also where I I there\'s a lot of opportunities for content creators. Look, I\'m always going to host this'

[09:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'channel, but I mean I think again, I think that she could fill in for me from time to time if if I just prep better. More interesting to me is that we are moving pretty quickly into real time. That\'s not just AI video. I mean that\'s holistically across the entire space.'

[09:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, I mean like what does a podcast with flame thrower girl look like? I don\'t know, but I\'m pretty sure I\'m going to get roasted pretty hard. But again, the only way that that really works is that if you\'ve got a character that is accepted. And of course, the only way to'

[10:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'do that is to put in the reps. So, if you\'re a content creator, or if you\'re thinking about becoming one, you know, start baking that in. Start playing with around with ideas and characters to fill out your roster. I do think at some point in the future, we\'re going to see'

[10:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'some interesting approaches using, you know, a human AI hybrid. So, you know, experiment. Use HeyGen. I mean there\'s a plethora of options and I mean it\'s pretty affordable. I mean ultimately, the big takeaway here is that none of'

[10:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this works if you don\'t have a plan. That\'s still the human part of it. Like you can\'t walk into a major like convention or event without, you know, some idea of what you\'re shooting as I learned yet again. And an AI avatar'

[10:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can\'t really make your video unless you know what your video is. So, again, as always, get your reps in. In the meantime, I thank you for watching. My name is Tim.'
